Refactor daemon pod connection ownership

Move pod runtime handles behind a PodConnection registry so the daemon
no longer owns separate per-pod proxy, tunnel, forwarding, and agent
maps.
The connection tracks host-gated reconnect state, SSE events, agent
session state, and local Codex and ssh-agent resources together.

This keeps host disconnect notifications and per-pod runtime ownership
in one place while preserving the existing daemon protocol behavior.
